TField "SumView.hstop" "<font color=\"#222222\" face=\"Arial, Tahoma, Helvetica, FreeSans, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.81818199157715px;\">A monadic formlet example</span></font><br><div><br></div><div class=\"post-body entry-content\" id=\"post-body-78074708202927443\" itemprop=\"description articleBody\" style=\"width: 730px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.4; position: relative; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Tahoma, Helvetica, FreeSans, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.google.es/search?q=formlets+haskell&amp;sourceid=ie7&amp;rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&amp;ie=&amp;oe=&amp;redir_esc=&amp;ei=d9LCUcenLsGphAeRqoH4BA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">Formlets</a>&nbsp;are about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.google.es/search?q=Applicative+haskell&amp;sourceid=ie7&amp;rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&amp;ie=&amp;oe=&amp;redir_esc=&amp;ei=utLCUcnKFo6ZhQfM64GgBA\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">applicative</a>&nbsp;instances, but what about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.google.es/search?q=monad+haskell&amp;sourceid=ie7&amp;rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&amp;ie=&amp;oe=&amp;redir_esc=&amp;ei=-9LCUfaKGc6DhQedroCACQ\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">monadic</a>&nbsp;instances? What a Monad instance of formlets means? I recently experimented with this and the results are very interesting -and powerful-. It mixes the best of web forms, with the flexibility of console applications.&nbsp;<br><br>Since the monad instance of the MFlow widgets (The View monad) stop at the first widget not validated or empty, and because a monad can manipulate output values of the widgets and therefore the result can be presented along the widget inputs, then the resulting interface is a mix of a console application, an spreadsheet and a dynamic HTML application that is programmed in plain simple imperative style without the need of javascript to achieve the dynamic behaviour</div></div>"